result.execSummary:
The defendant Brian S Dutcher was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant appears in court with Attorney Mettelka. DA Hayes appears in court for the State of Wisconsin.   Plea questionnaire filed.  Rights given.  Court finds that defendant is knowingly and voluntarily waiving right to jury trial and plea is found to be entered knowingly and voluntarily.  Found guilty. Count 1: no contest. Court adopts the recommendation. Court finds the Defendant guilty and orders 10 days in jail imposed and stayed and places the Defendant on 12 months probation. Conditions,   AODA assessment and follow through with any counseling or treatment deemed appropriate by agent, continue with counseling that is being received right now, Maintain absolute sobriety. 2 days credit noted. DNA sample, court costs at $443.00 to be paid to the clerk of courts within 60 days or set up payment plan. To run concurrent with 21CM304.
